subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Tetra smilaxis
Xue, Song & Hong, 2006a, but can be differentiated from the latter by opisthosoma with dark shading on rear annular margins (dark shading absent in 
Tetra smilaxis
), prodorsal shield as wide as opisthosoma (opisthosoma wider than prodorsal shield in 
Tetra smilaxis
), admedian lines connected at basal 1/3 but separate at basal 2/3 of prodorsal shield (admedian lines connected at basal 1/3 and basal 2/3 of prodorsal shield in 
Tetra smilaxis
).
